  "text": "Another generative dependency model of interest is that given by [CITATION_1] . In this model the sentence and tree are generated jointly, which allows one to drop the assumption that p(T |n) is uniform. This requires the addition to the model of parameters p x,STOP for each x ∈ Σ, with the normalization condition p x,STOP + y,k p k x,y = 1. It is possible to extend the model of [CITATION_2] to the non-projective case. However, the resulting distribution will be over multisets of words from the alphabet instead of strings. The discussion in this section is stated for the model in [CITATION_3] ; a similar treatment can be developed for the model in [CITATION_4] .",
